Ifeoluwa Oyerinde The Abuja zonal office of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission has apprehended one Ajayiton Harry and two others for alleged involvement in Internet fraud and other cybercrimes. The suspects were arrested at their hideout, Flat G2, Plot 334, Dawaki, behind News Engineering, Abuja, following complaints by concerned citizens in the area. Among the items recovered from the suspects are two Lexus R350 SUVs, three laptops and phones. The commission stated that the suspects would be charged as soon as investigation into the case was concluded. Copyright PUNCH.
